elation for both late-type and S0 galaxies. These discrepancies can be\nreconciled if one considers the two peaks as two different components.\nConsidering the morphological biases in favour, bulge-dominated galaxies and\nstar-formation central enhancement, we suggest a scenario of multiple\nsequential minor mergers driving the increase of the bulge size, leading to\nlarger fractions of S0 galaxies and a deficit of pure disc galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jul 2020 18:00:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-30"}
