\nsignificant when the ratio of observation frequencies and cut-off frequency\n$\\nu_{\\rm obs}/\\nu_{\\infty,0} \\gtrsim 10^{-3}$, corresponding to $\\sim 3 \\cdot\n10^2$ MHz. For viewing angles $\\vartheta \\lesssim -30^{\\circ}$, a DDRG\nmorphology can no longer be recognized. The second jets must be injected within\n$\\lesssim$ 4 per cent of the lifetime of the first jets for a DDRG structure to\nemerge, which is relevant for Active Galactic Nuclei feedback constraints.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jul 2020 13:05:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-30"}
